Privacy Policy for DepositQuery
Effective Date: 12/30/2024
RM Financial Consulting ("we," "us," "our") values your trust and is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use the DepositQuery application ("Application").
By using the Application, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please refrain from using the Application.
________________________________________
1. Information We Collect
DepositQuery integrates with QuickBooks Online (QBO) and may collect the following types of information:
1.	Account Information: Data associated with your QBO account, such as your company name, account ID, and user credentials required to connect to QBO.
2.	Transaction Data: Invoice, payment, and deposit records accessed through QBO, including amounts, dates, customer information, and related financial data.
3.	Usage Data: Information about your use of the Application, such as access times, device details, and error reports.
________________________________________
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:
1.	Provide and improve the functionality of DepositQuery.
2.	Identify unpaid invoices and facilitate the creation of related payments and deposits in QBO.
3.	Respond to your inquiries, provide customer support, and address technical issues.
4.	Comply with legal and regulatory obligations.
________________________________________
3. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell or share your data with third parties, except in the following circumstances:
1.	Service Providers: Trusted third-party vendors who assist us in delivering the Application (e.g., hosting or analytics services).
2.	Legal Compliance: When required by law or to protect our legal rights.
3.	User Consent: If you provide explicit consent for data sharing.
________________________________________
4. Data Security
We employ industry-standard measures to protect your information, including encryption and secure data storage. While we strive to protect your data, no method of transmission or storage is entirely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
________________________________________
5. Integration with QuickBooks Online
DepositQuery operates as a third-party application and integrates directly with QuickBooks Online. By using DepositQuery, you agree to the following:
1.	You have authorized DepositQuery to access and process your QBO data.
2.	Data retrieved from QBO will only be used for the purposes stated in this Privacy Policy.
3.	Use of DepositQuery must comply with Intuit's developer policies and QuickBooks Online Terms of Service.
________________________________________
6. Retention of Information
We retain your information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy or as required by law.
________________________________________
7. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your data:
1.	Access and download your data.
2.	Request correction or deletion of your data.
3.	Restrict or object to data processing.
________________________________________
8. Third-Party Services
DepositQuery may link to or integrate with third-party services, including QuickBooks Online. This Privacy Policy does not cover the practices of these third parties. Please review their respective privacy policies for more information.
________________________________________
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for legal compliance. We will notify you of significant updates via email or through the Application.
________________________________________
10. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our practices, please contact us at:
